'''Samuel Albert Alain Arcade Moutoussamy''' (born 12 August 1996) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[defensive midfielder]] for [[Super League Greece|Greek Super League]] club [[Atromitos F.C.|Atromitos]]. Born in France, he plays for the [[DR Congo national football team|DR Congo national team]].

==Club career==
[[File:RC Lens - FC Nantes (28-10-2023) 16 (cropped).jpg|left|thumb|294x294px|Moutoussamy with [[FC Nantes|Nantes]] in 2023]]
Moutoussamy made his professional debut for [[FC Nantes|Nantes]] in a 1–0 [[Ligue 1]] loss to [[Olympique de Marseille|Marseille]] on 12 August 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lfp.fr/ligue1/feuille_match/82832|title=LFP.fr - Ligue de Football Professionnel - Ligue 1 Conforama - Saison 2017/2018 - 2ème journée - FC Nantes / Olympique de Marseille|website=www.lfp.fr}}</ref> On 6 October 2020, he joined [[Fortuna Sittard]] on loan.<ref>{{cite press release|url=https://www.fortunasittard.nl/samuel-moutoussamy-tweede-aanwinst-op-deadlineday/|title=SAMUEL MOUTOUSSAMY TWEEDE AANWINST OP DEADLINEDAY|publisher=[[Fortuna Sittard]]|date=6 October 2020|access-date=26 October 2020|language=nl|archive-date=15 October 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221015044646/https://www.fortunasittard.nl/samuel-moutoussamy-tweede-aanwinst-op-deadlineday/|url-status=dead}}</ref>

On 29 January 2023, in the 0–0 draw against [[Clermont Foot]], he played his 100th game in [[Ligue 1]] with Nantes. Three days later, the club rewarded him for the achievement.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fcnantes.com/articles/article2809.php?num=42030|title=SAMUEL MOUTOUSSAMY À L'HONNEUR EN AVANT-MATCH|date=2 February 2023|access-date=2 February 2023|language=fr}}</ref>

==International career==
Moutoussamy was born in metropolitan France to an [[Indo-Guadeloupean]] father and a Congolese mother.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Lavon |first=Steven |date=17 May 2019 |title=Samuel Moutoussamy: il ouvre la porte à la RDC |url=https://www.africatopsports.com/2019/05/17/samuel-moutoussamy-il-ouvre-la-porte-a-la-rdc/}}</ref> He debuted for the [[DR Congo national football team|DR Congo national team]] in a 1–1 [[Friendly (association football)|friendly]] tie with [[Algeria national football team|Algeria]] on 10 October 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fcnantes.com/articles/article2809.php?num=31821|title=Internationaux – Résultats et programme des Nantais !|website=FR}}</ref>

On 27 December 2023, he was selected from the list of 24 Congolese players selected by [[Sébastien Desabre]] to compete in the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations]].

==Personal life==
He was born in [[Paris]], France. His mother is [[Demographics of the Democratic Republic of the Congo|Congolese]], and his father is [[Indo-Guadeloupeans|Indo-Guadeloupean]] of [[Tamils|Tamil]] origin.

